description.narrative: In 2019, UNICEF technical and financial support to nutrition surveys enabled improved quality of assessment and monitoring of trends at national and state levels. UNICEF supported routine data collection, bottleneck analysis of selected nutrition interventions and development of performance score card in all ten states. The evidence-based planning and performance score card enhanced development of partnership agreements with 40 civil society organizations for scale up of nutrition services. UNICEF's contribution to strengthen nutrition governance resulted in development and endorsement from Ministry of Health on a Multisectoral Nutrition Strategic Roadmap. UNICEF supported one publication on Community Management of Acute Malnutrition | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
